THIRD-PARTY SOFTWARE NOTICES AND INFORMATION

This application incorporates components from the projects listed below.

================================================================================

1. droidVNC-NG (Original Android Application)
   Copyright (C) 2020 Christian Beier
   License: GPL-2.0
   Source: https://github.com/bk138/droidVNC-NG

   This application is a fork of droidVNC-NG with the native VNC server
   implementation replaced with a Rust-based implementation.

================================================================================

2. rustvncserver (VNC Server Library)
   Copyright (C) 2025 Dustin McAfee
   License: Apache-2.0

   Pure Rust VNC (RFB) server implementation used by this application.

   This library implements the VNC protocol as specified in RFC 6143 and
   includes the following third-party components:

   - ZYWRLE Algorithm
     Copyright 2006 by Hitachi Systems & Services, Ltd.
     (Noriaki Yamazaki, Research & Development Center)
     Used under BSD-style license

   - Rust Dependencies (all compatible with GPL-2.0):
     * tokio (MIT License)
     * bytes (MIT License)
     * flate2 (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
     * png (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
     * log (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
     * thiserror (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
     * des (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
     * rand (MIT OR Apache-2.0)

================================================================================

3. libjpeg-turbo
   License: BSD-style (IJG, Modified BSD, zlib)
   Source: https://libjpeg-turbo.org/

   High-performance JPEG codec used for Tight encoding with JPEG compression.

================================================================================

4. noVNC
   License: MPL-2.0
   Source: https://github.com/novnc/noVNC

   HTML5 VNC client included for browser-based access.

